      <part part_index="2" name="Chicago airport to hire goats" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="129">
            	<![CDATA[
A Chicago airport wants to hire goats to trim the grass.
The Chicago Department of Aviation (芝加哥航空部门) has put out an ad for the goats. They want to bring in thirty of the animals to eat grass and weeds (杂草) in an area that's hard to reach with a lawn mower (割草机).
They think goats will be more environmentally friendly than using a mower and other chemicals to keep the grass in check. They're also planning to hire a goat herder (牧羊人) to look after them.
The grass is protected by a security fence (安全隔离墙), so the goats won't be in any danger of getting onto the runway.
Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport (亚特兰大哈兹菲尔德-杰克逊国际机场) in the U.S. has also started using sheep to trim the grass and San Francisco International Airport has been using goats for years.
           	]]>
            </article>
